clever way of looking at the

00:11:50.350 --> 00:11:53.970
basic needs of a mobile
web user, or

00:11:53.970 --> 00:11:56.260
just a web user really.

00:11:56.260 --> 00:11:59.590
And it's based on Maslow's
hierarchy of needs.

00:11:59.590 --> 00:12:03.310
We, as human beings,
have certain needs.

00:12:03.310 --> 00:12:06.110
And some of those needs are more
important than others.

00:12:06.110 --> 00:12:08.870
Some are prerequisites
for achieving the

00:12:08.870 --> 00:12:11.680
next level of self.

00:12:11.680 --> 00:12:13.750
So at the bottom of the
heap, we have our

00:12:13.750 --> 00:12:15.330
physiological needs.

00:12:15.330 --> 00:12:16.630
We need to be able to breathe.

00:12:16.630 --> 00:12:20.595
We need to be able to eat, and
drink, and sleep, and all of

00:12:20.595 --> 00:12:21.040
that stuff.

00:12:21.040 --> 00:12:22.930
So that's really important.

00:12:22.930 --> 00:12:27.680
But then, as you climb the
pyramid a little bit, we have

00:12:27.680 --> 00:12:30.790
a sense of safety, a sense
of love, a sense of

00:12:30.790 --> 00:12:32.980
self-actualization, and
all of that stuff.

00:12:32.980 --> 00:12:36.230
So those are sort of considered
nice-to-haves

00:12:36.230 --> 00:12:38.120
whenever you put them
side by side to

00:12:38.120 --> 00:12:39.820
something like breathing.

00:12:39.820 --> 00:12:42.490
So what Christopher did was
something very clever.

00:12:42.490 --> 00:12:45.220
And he basically translated
those into the

00:12:45.220 --> 00:12:48.020
